					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If you enter the relevant password into the <a href="http://games.technoplaza.net/mpg/" class="postlink">Metroid Password Generator</a>, it says &quot;Invalid password: Reset bit is set&quot;.<br /><br />If you read the corresponding technical documentation, it says:<br /><div class="quotetitle"><a href="http://games.technoplaza.net/mpg/password.txt" class="postlink">http://games.technoplaza.net/mpg/password.txt</a> wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The reset bit is part of the start location. There are 16 possible values, but only 5 valid ones. Turning on the reset bit will produce and invalid start location and cause Metroid to reset. This is why it is called it is called the reset bit, because it guarantees an invalid password.</div><br /><br />So at least you know where to look.</div>

